138
00:10:39,620 --> 00:10:45,323
It's weekly trash collection in a 64-gallon cart, often referred to as a toter.

139
00:10:45,423 --> 00:10:48,004
Some people call it a bin, some people call it a barrel.

140
00:10:48,685 --> 00:10:50,426
It's a 64-gallon cart tonight.

141
00:10:51,492 --> 00:10:58,774
overflow bags are used by some folks 33 gallon bags they cost $2 a bag on a per bag basis.

142
00:10:59,795 --> 00:11:04,416
There's every other week recycling in a 96 gallon cart.

143
00:11:05,337 --> 00:11:09,758
Their seasonal leaf collections right now it's 15 weeks per year.

144
00:11:10,638 --> 00:11:12,499
There's bulky items collection.

145
00:11:12,599 --> 00:11:18,401
There's no cost and no real limit to what folks can throw out over the course of the year.

146
00:11:19,572 --> 00:11:25,017
And then there's a white goods collection service for $26 per item.

147
00:11:27,359 --> 00:11:34,986
So how does Medford compare to trash, to other communities in terms of trash disposal?

148
00:11:35,066 --> 00:11:44,395
This is a chart from MassDEP for 2021 data that was reported by communities all across Massachusetts

149
00:11:44,788 --> 00:11:49,411
